news.title: Ahmedabad: Occupant's name to be removed from residential property tax bill
news.para: "Property tax amount remains unchanged regardless of whether the property is occupied by the owner or if has been given on rent,” said Jainik Vakil, chairman of AMC’s revenue committee.

news.title: The Executive Centre to invest Rs 200 crore for expansion in three cities
news.para: The flexible workspace industry has become more relevant for organisations amid the pandemic as companies across sectors reassess their real estate holdings, both long-term and short-term, to make capital expenditure more efficient.

news.title: Tax relief on bonds to offset property sale gain stands despite broker delay: ITAT
news.para: Income-tax liability that arises from long-term capital gains on sale of immovable property can be reduced by purchase of bonds eligible under section 54-EC. However, to avail of the exemption, it is vital that the investment is made within six months of the sale of the property.

news.title: Maharashtra nod to not revise capital value of buildings, land in Mumbai
news.para: Under the Mumbai Municipal Corporation Act, 1888, the capital value, based on which property tax is paid, is to be revised every five years.

news.title: Noida authority razes 26 structures in four housing societies
news.para: The anti-demolition team deputed by the Authority, along with a police force, carried out the drive against illegal structures in two projects of AIMS Max Gardenia in Sector 75, Eldeco Amantram in Sector 119 and Homes 121 in Sector 121.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces to jointly develop 4.8-acre land parcel in Dahisar
news.para: The project will offer approximately 5 lakh sq. ft. of carpet area. Mahindra Lifespaces recently reported a consolidated net profit of Rs 13.23 crore for the quarter ended September 2021.

news.title: A month left, but no plan yet to bring down Supertech twin towers
news.para: On Wednesday, a meeting among officials of three different companies, Noida Authority and demolition experts from the US and UK was held. But none of the participants could come up with any concrete plan.

news.title: Unitech appoints Ashok Kumar Yadav as new CEO
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Unitech informed that the Board of Directors has redesignated/ appointed Ashok Kumar Yadav, Chief Operating Officer, as the Chief Executive Officer of the Unitech Group. The appointment has been made with immediate effect.

news.title: Sagar Cements' net profit dips 59% to Rs 20.76 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 371.50 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 13 per cent from Rs 329.17 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat net profit dips 7% to Rs 214 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,622 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 11 per cent from Rs 2,353 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Spanish cabinet approves bill penalising empty homes, rewarding lower rents
news.para: Under the law, regional governments can declare areas as in "high demand" when the average household spends over 30% of its net income on rent or mortgage costs and bills and if property prices have risen more than 5% above inflation.

news.title: New homes sales jump 14% in US in September 2021
news.para: New home sales jumped 14.0% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 800,000 units last month, the highest level since March, the Commerce Department said on Tuesday.

news.title: PIL seeks appointment of Gujarat REAT's chairman, technical member
news.para: “Since the function of the tribunal is purely judicial and adjudicatory, keeping in view the doctrine of separation of powers…, the government ideally should have a minimal say in the functioning of the tribunal,” the plea said. “It is, however, manifest that ‘Administration of Justice’ is a subject matter of the Department of Justice under the Ministry of Law and Justice.”

news.title: Shriram Housing Finance posts net profit of Rs 18.8 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: ​Disbursements were better than the pre-pandemic levels at Rs 633 crore compared to Rs 517 crore in Q2FY21 and Rs 221 crore in Q1FY22, Ravi Subramanian, MD & CEO of the company said, adding asset quality improved with gross stage 3 assets improving by 36 bps to 1.72 per cent.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji in talks with global funds to set up $1.5 billion Investment Platforms
news.para: Each of these joint investment platforms will have equity funding of $500 million and will be investing close to $1 billion, including the leverage, in these real estate segments that are emerging as independent asset classes with strong growth potential, they said.
